HEADWORD: Tram
<hw>Tram</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Trammel</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 6.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tram</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Tram
<hw>Tram</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Trammed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tramming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To convey or transport on a
tramway or on a tram car.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tram</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Tram
<hw>Tram</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To operate, or conduct the business
of, a tramway; to travel by tramway.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trama</ent>⟦br⟧
